        "text_Xeh8E7": {
          "type": "text",
          "name": "t:names.text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>We met in Bihar while working on economic development research. What began as a shared interest in systems change slowly grew into something more personal. Long conversations about food, health, farmers, and the quiet gaps between what is grown and what finally reaches our plates led to the birth of <strong>The Boring Foods Company</strong>.</p><p>As we travelled across the country, meeting smallholder farmers, traders, and wholesalers, a pattern became impossible to ignore. Farmers doing careful, honest work were often being shortchanged. On the other side, customers were rarely getting access to truly high-quality, clean products.</p><p>We went deeper into food systems, health research, supply chains, and traditional knowledge. What we found was surprisingly simple. Good health does not need to be complicated. It does not need constant trends, loud claims, or confusing ingredients.</p><p>With backgrounds in impact evaluation, agri-tech, and digital inclusion, we bring a data-driven lens to deeply human problems. We believe in transparent supply chains, the power of indigenous knowledge, and that simple, honest food builds lasting trust.</p><p>Our long-term vision is to help build strong, preventative, foundational health. We believe that small, sustainable changes made every day create lasting impact, not fads or shortcuts. We want to grow a community of people who feel empowered about what goes into their bodies, who ask questions, read labels, and make informed decisions with confidence, not fear.</p><p>The Boring Foods Company is our way of cutting through the noise and misinformation around health, and coming back to what truly matters. Clean ingredients, real science, and food you can trust.</p>",
            "width": "fit-content",
            "max_width": "none",
            "alignment": "left",
            "type_preset": "rte",
            "font": "var(--font-body--family)",
            "font_size": "1rem",
